## Document IDs

All document IDs share one project prefix and a daily, zero-padded sequence — each document type counts its own subfolder independently, so a ticket and a proposal opened the same day can both be `#001`.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Prefix | `{{TICKET_PREFIX}}` |
| Date format | DDMMYYYY |
| Sequence | 3-digit zero-padded, resets daily, per document type |

| Document | Format | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Ticket | `{PREFIX}{DDMMYYYY}{SEQ}` | `{{TICKET_PREFIX}}29062026001` |
| Proposal | `{PREFIX}P{DDMMYYYY}{SEQ}` | `{{TICKET_PREFIX}}P29062026001` |
| Request Note | `{PREFIX}R{DDMMYYYY}{SEQ}` | `{{TICKET_PREFIX}}R29062026001` |
| Invoice | `{PREFIX}I{DDMMYYYY}{SEQ}` | `{{TICKET_PREFIX}}I29062026001` |

Change `Prefix` to match your client-facing code (e.g. `XYZ`, `ACM`, `MDB`).

